3.4

\[ \begin{aligned} x_{t} &= \beta_{0} + \beta_{1}.t + w_{t} \\ E(x_{t}) &= \beta_{0} + \beta_{1}.t \end{aligned} \]

The mean is not constant, so this is not stationary.

\[ \begin{aligned} \nabla x_{t} = x_{t} - x_{t-1} &= \beta_{0} + \beta_{1}.t + w_{t} - \beta_{0} - \beta_{1}.(t-1) - w_{t-1} \\ &= \beta_{1} + w_{t} - w_{t-1} \\ E(\nabla x_{t}) &= \beta_{1} \\ \gamma_{\nabla x_{t}}(h) &= Cov(\nabla x_{t}, \nabla x_{t+h}) \\ h=0,\gamma(0) &= Var(\nabla x_{t}) = 0 \\ h=1, \gamma(1) &= Cov(\beta_{1}+w_{t}-w_{t-1}, \beta_{1} + w_{t+1} - w_{t}) \\ &= -\sigma_{w}^2 \\ h =2, \gamma(2) &= Cov(\beta_{1}+w_{t}-w_{t-1}, \beta_{1} + w_{t+2} - w_{t+1}) \\ &= 0 \end{aligned} \]

Since, the mean is constant, and the autocovariance is only dependent on h, it is stationary.

\[ \begin{aligned} x_t &= \beta_0 + \beta_1 t + y_t \\ \nabla x_t &= x_t - x_{t-1} \\ \nabla x_t &= (\beta_0 + \beta_1 t + y_t) - (\beta_0 + \beta_1 (t-1) + y_{t-1})\\ \nabla x_t &= \beta_1 + y_t - y_{t-1}\\ E[\nabla x_t] &= E[\beta_1 + y_t - y_{t-1}]\\ E[\nabla x_t] &= \beta_1 + \mu_y - \mu_y = \beta_1\\ \gamma_{\nabla x}(h) &= \text{Cov}(\nabla x_t, \nabla x_{t+h})\\ \gamma_{\nabla x}(h) &= \text{Cov}(\beta_1 + y_t - y_{t-1}, \beta_1 + y_{t+h} - y_{t+h-1})\\ \gamma_{\nabla x}(h) &= \text{Cov}(y_t - y_{t-1}, y_{t+h} - y_{t+h-1})\\ \gamma_{\nabla x}(h) &= \gamma_y(0) + \gamma_y(0) - \gamma_y(h-1) - \gamma_y(h+1)\\ \end{aligned} \]

3.5

\[ \begin{aligned} E[x_t - x_{t-1}] &= E[\delta + w_t + y_t - y_{t-1}] \\ E[x_t - x_{t-1}] &= \delta + E[w_t] + E[y_t - y_{t-1}] \\ E[x_t - x_{t-1}] &= \delta \\ Var(x_t - x_{t-1}) &= Var(\delta + w_t + y_t - y_{t-1}) \\ Var(x_t - x_{t-1}) &= Var(w_t + y_t - y_{t-1}) \\ \gamma(h) &= Cov(x_t - x_{t-1}, x_{t-h} - x_{t-h-1}) \\ \gamma(h) &= Cov(\delta + w_t + y_t - y_{t-1}, \delta + w_{t-h} + y_{t-h} - y_{t-h-1}) \\ \gamma(h) &= Cov(w_t + y_t - y_{t-1}, w_{t-h} + y_{t-h} - y_{t-h-1}) \end{aligned} \]

The mean is constant, Variance is constant, and autocovariance is only dependent on h, so it is stationary.

3.8

plot(soi, col=rgb(0.5, 0.6, 0.85, .9))
lines(lowess(soi, f=.05), lwd=2, col=4) 
lo = predict(loess(soi~ time(soi)), se=TRUE)
trnd = ts(lo$fit, start=1950, freq=12) 
lines(trnd, col=6, lwd=2)
L = trnd - qt(0.975, lo$df)*lo$se
U = trnd + qt(0.975, lo$df)*lo$se
xx = c(time(soi), rev(time(soi)))
yy = c(L, rev(U))
polygon(xx, yy, border=8, col=gray(.6, alpha=.4) )

# sinusoidal
trnd = time(soi)
C4 = cos(2*pi*trnd/4)
S4 = sin(2*pi*trnd/4)

sinusoidal_model = lm(soi ~ trnd + C4 + S4)
predicted = fitted(sinusoidal_model)

# lines(soi)
lines(predicted, col="red")

THe sinusoidal model is withing the confidence interval of lowess model.
